Class Candidate

java.lang.Object
Candidate
All Implemented Interfaces:
IRepresentative
public class Candidate extends Object implements IRepresentative
A Candidate represents a candidate in an IR election. Implements IRepresentative, an interface used for outlining a representative in an election.

    • Candidate

      public Candidate(String partyName, String candidateName)
      Constructor for a Candidate object, creates a Candidate with specified party name and candidate name. Used to create Candidates when first reading from the election information csv file.
      Parameters:
      partyName - the name of the political party the candidate belongs to, Ex: Democrat.
      candidateName - the candidate's name, Ex: Biden.
